I think they should be 100% PAL/SK, and this is where VI partially failed.<br>
Now they seem (in my warrior's point of vue) to reconsider these classes by giving them new *unique* spells/abilities for knights.<br>
Honestly, this is fine to me and to many others warriors. Like stated *many times* before in this very thread, we're *happy* to what happen to you, guys. Really.<br>
<br>
Hell, we will even be *happy* of seeing you tanking *IF*, and only *IF*, we, on the other hand, had something &quot;special&quot;, a warrior's thing, that would balance this fact.<br>
Actually, our only role is tanking. Seeing monks or knights do this with around the same success, *WITH* a much better aggro control, that my friends is bothering us.<br>
<br>
Moreover, our only eye-candy thingie, critical hits, has been removed to us. <br>
Giving this to wizards I agree, they are the specialized mana warriors, as we are the specialized melee warriors. Giving this to everyone else was a mistake.<br>
This was not even very useful, but this at least was our only class-specific thing (no, don't speak me about defensive, I would give it for free if I could).<br>
<br>
I think we should stop arguing over and over about PAL/WAR comparisons, and let's trying together to find a good solution, *AND* to submit it to VI (if they are willing to understand us, and I doubt it seeing Absor's posts).<br>
Stop coming here just to say we, warriors, should be happy with what we have, this is not true.<br>
<br>
To summarize, actual problems are :<br>
- We're no longer masters of tanking, considering the fact that aggro-control (and, to a larger extent, raid DPS) is to be considered at. <br>
This is due to : <br>
* almost-infinite mana for casters, especially clerics (KEI, ManaRod2, Bards, FT, ...). <br>
* AC-Softcap that almost every melee can reach with little efforts (cultural trade skills, no more WAR&gt;PAL/SK&gt;All AC-Gear graduation, and so on)<br>
* AAXP, for those able to reach the third page (we, warriors, have no AA to help in our job, apart from AE Taunt).<br>
* the amount of 100HP ALL/ALL items, reducing even further the HP gap between warriors and others class.<br>
<br>
- Other problem is our DPS, that no longer is way ahead from knights. Seeing monks, rangers and rogue do a lot more than us isn't a problem, and I feel even happy for rangers that AT LAST get something to do with their bows.<br>
Knights and Warriors might be equals in OVERALL DPS, by this I mean Melee + Spells, but there should be a noticeable gap between melee-only DPS. So, Knights should do 80% Warrior's DPS + 20% by spells to fill the gap.<br>
There is something to do here, and I see these possible improvements :<br>
* Increase Warriors DPS by, say, giving a bonus for offhand weapon. I don't know if this shock only me, but dual wield should do overall better damage than 2Handers, this makes sense ! This will profit to all dual-wielding classes.<br>
* In the same time, give something to PAL/SK to do the DPS they miss by spells. In cleric's manner for PAL, in a necromancer's manner for SK (maybe for these two add a lure-dot, to help them landing something on boss mobs <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
* This idea is not mine but it is so far the best I saw here : increase mitigation for plate class, respecting the : WAR&gt;PAL/SK&gt;All in mitigation. With this improvement, knights would be better at tanking BUT warriors will be even better, the gap is preserved, and *NOT* with this crap shield idea.<br>
* Look at not no-drop items +100HP All/All, and make them class specific, or change them. Not no drop, because changing no-drop item would be not fair at all.  <p><img src="http://perso.wanadoo.fr/mcduck/images/signature.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugazzaztsmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GazzazTSMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/29/02 5:25:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1109.topic&index=325>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hybrid Niche?</span><hr size=1> Gamdwin,<br>
