<br>
-Warriors taunt is screwy from 50-60, in that anything that cons higher level cannot be taunted.  I agree that this should definitely be fixed.  In fact, even mobs higher than level 60 should be tauntable.  Maybe Verant should code specific mobs that aren't tauntable, though.  After all, you have to figure some critters out there are smart enough to ignore the warrior poking it with a couple puny weapons, and focus on the wizard blasting it with magical fireballs instead.  Taunt should work on most creatures, regardless of level.<br>
<br>
-Knights with lots of AAXP (and Monks, to a lesser(?) extent), with (very) high end gear are able to encroach on the warrior main tank nicheas regards both hp and AC.  I can certainly understand why this would be an issue for warriors (especially the monks!), although I think I understand that it only happens at the very highest levels of the game.  This might not need a fix if it only affects the top .1% of the game, but it should be examined closely.  Broken is broken, after all.  Lots of good ideas here on how to fix it, so I won't delve any deeper into that.<br>
<br>
-Warriors can't fill any other role on a raid/in an xp group other than tank effectively, because their damage output rates about the same as or a bit better than a knight class similarly equipped (and they don't have the spells or abilities the Knights or Monks have).  I would suggest requesting that your offensive disciplines be improved DRAMATICALLY.  I won't make up numbers, because I don't know exactly how much more DPS output you need, nor do I know how much DPS each offensive discipline adds.  I'm just suggesting this as one way to make warriors a viable DPS class if they aren't needed to be MT.<br>
<br>
Have I identified all the major issues?  I agree that the shield changes don't look like they will really be all that stellar for Warriors, although I can imagine a few tweaks that Verant might make that could really change that.  If I've left something out, it was done honestly, I didn't intentionally fail to list anything.<br>
<br>
-Aragir<br>
<br>
