<br>
Anyway, I'm glad we agree that Verant is (and should be) moving towards each class having a role in the raid-level game.  Hopefully between these threads and our discussions at PON, paladins will be able to come up with something we can suggest that won't infringe on the role of warriors, and vice versa.<br>
<br>
Also, regarding the highest end stuff trickling down, I'm sure that's true to a degree.  However, based on my experience, a lot of people are still TRYING to get into TOV, so end-game issues don't affect 99.9% of the people I know.  I don't know if I know a representative cross-section of the EQ population or not, but I doubt very heartily that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> I'll</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> ever see a monk main- or even Rampage-tanking.  So, while I agree that it's an issue that should be looked at, I think it should be balanced at that end of the game, possibly with items, rather than balanced by changing the classes across the entire spectrum of levels (where most classes aren't broken or even out-of-whack at the moment).<br>
<br>
